Text.Value: Now leave. I have a battle to return to.
It is the reason She mobilised Her people to retrieve the Astral Prism.
My killer. So you are not to be trusted.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Daisy reforms from astral ether on the spot where they were killed. The player is shocked to see Daisy alive.
EditorData.NodeContext: with an undercurrent of bitter disappointment

Text.Value: Then again, you always were special, Lae'zel.
You've been appearing to me as Vlaakith. How?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player takes the blade and drives it through Daisy's chest. Daisy reacts with pain.

Text.Value: Thank you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Daisy stands up. Makes the sword vanish with a gesture of the hand.

Text.Value: You know more. What else can you tell me?
The real Vlaakith is lying to you. You think She knows the secret mother Gith used to crush the mind flayer empire.
Yet your queen wants you to kill me. I will not stand in your way.
Hm. Ever since the Astral Prism was stolen from Her oh-so-secret hiding place for it, She has become desperate. She lies.
Dear Lae'zel. I had hoped you'd see reason.
A beautiful lie. But a lie nonetheless.
So you found a way in.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: On seeing us, Daisy stands up and turns to face us. With a gesture of the hand, invites us to come closer.

Text.Value: Vlakith, my Queen. I don't understand.
You wasted no time, Lae'zel. No Queen could ask for a more faithful disciple.
I suppose I can't blame you. You are threatened by the tadpole and you think I prevented you from being cured.
Who are you fighting?
Get up. You will not die today.
There's no lie. I would never lie to you.
Launch into a lengthy monologue using the biggest words you know.
I think I may have overestimated your intelligence. You would simply not understand.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Daisy gives you a long stare, unimpressed. Then recovers before speaking.

Text.Value: You see, I know Vlaakith's secret.
You will be marked for death, yes.
Even now, Vlaakith sends word to your people. They will stalk you to Toril's edge.
Must you? Really? If you were going to do it, at least you could have tried harder than that.
She is trying Her very best to kill me. By sending you.
This is all wrong. Queen Vlaakith would never lie to Her people.
A prison. Commissioned by Vlaakith, built in the Hells. A place for all who threaten her to wilt and die.
But that very secret, which Vlaakith only pretends to know, is how I've been protecting you.
A secret so important that She would preserve it at any cost - including sacrificing the very power that would stop the Grand Design - me.
I can hear your thoughts. You think I'm lying. Vlaakith warned that I would try to deceive you. But consider this - what reason have I to deceive you? I want the same thing as you - freedom.
And discover for yourself the true nature of your Queen.
Why did you stop the zaith'isk from removing my tadpole?
Try to probe into the figure's mind.
*In spite of your reservations, she's telling the truth.*
*In spite of your reservations, he's telling the truth.*
*In spite of your reservations, they're telling the truth.*
This is the only place it cannot reach me.
Wait, aren't you supposed to be dead?
Though your judgement leaves much to be desired, your conviction, as ever, is strong.

EditorData.NodeContext: like a teacher disappointed by a naughty child whose behaviour they fully expected

Text.Value: Try to kill the figure again.
All you need to know is that it is enough for Vlaakith to want me dead.
It's a truth. The third truth. Of the Maltbianblake spell. Obviously.
But unlike you, unlike anyone else in any plane, I know Vlaakith's secret.
It is the very least of Queen Vlaakith's deceptions.
Fewer still would change their mind.
Denial is more potent than magic itself. And far harder to lift.
Out there, I would perish, and with my protection gone, you would become a mind flayer.
Live with it, if you must. But if you wish to be free of the illithid threat, heed my instruction.
I am not Vlaakith, child. But I am your safety and your salvation.
I don't know.
The stuff of nightmares, and no concern of yours. It is enough that Vlaakith hunts me for my knowledge.
I will not shirk my duty.
Your survival depends on mine, and mine on yours. It's less than ideal, but it is where we stand.
That was uncalled for. Though, a spell well cast.
A secret that I know, and Vlaakith doesn't.
You claim to know a lot about my Queen, and yet you present no evidence.
Godlike in power, yes. But with none of the sanctity. A false god who lies to her own people.
It is why She sent you to kill me. And why She will kill you once you leave this place.
There is no third axiom.
I have delayed long enough. The next attack is overdue, and I can't risk you being caught in the middle of it. I need you out there, searching for the Absolute.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: In the distance, sounds of battle (same as we heard in the first dream), darkening skies. A military order is given to attack. Daisy glances over their shoulder.

Text.Value: A secret so great that if Her people ever found out, that would be the end of Her rule, the end of Her.
I stand by my choice.
And yet if you spare me, you make an enemy of Vlaakith. And you already have an enemy in the Absolute.
I don't intend to make a habit of conversing with my killer, so I will be brief.
If you're such a threat to Her, why hasn't She killed you already?
But between Vlaakith and the Absolute, it is the Absolute I fear more. You would do well to think the same.
I suppose She hoped to extract it from my corpse. How She intended to do that, I know not. It is a desperate act driven by fear.
I hope you are ready to face Vlaakith's wrath.
Believe me or don't. The queen has already spoken.
You are an agent of the Grand Design. Vlaakith told me so.
And now that you know the truth, what will you do?
She will be furious. She fears nothing more than the loss of Her empire. The knowledge I have of Her deception will bring that about.
Go on then. If you must.
And you will learn to live with them.
Vlaakith's a god. What could you possibly know that would bring down Her empire?
Queen Vlaakith is a god. What could you possibly know that would bring Her down?
*A palace of memories opens up to you, separated into segments. Within one segment, you see it - the truth, exactly as the figure said. She saved your life.*
*A palace of memories opens up to you, separated into segments. Within one segment, you see it - the truth, exactly as the figure said. He saved your life.*
*A palace of memories opens up to you, separated into segments. Within one segment, you see it - the truth, exactly as the figure said. They saved your life.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Just focus on player face as their mind is blown.

Text.Value: But She does not. If the illithids would ever rise to power again, She would be incapable of stopping them.
If Her deception were ever to come to light, Her impotence, Her rule would be over.
Few githyanki would deny their Queen's orders.
Even now, the Inquisitor awaits your return, ready to strike.
Tell me - do you know the third axiom of the Maltbianblake incantation?
It's impossible. At least for now. The secret I carry is not only a threat to Vlaakith but also to the Absolute. And it is the latter I fear the most.
Ah - your mind seeks answers. I feel it reaching, stretching, contorting. Yet still coming up short.
Your people had no intention of letting you survive purification. And I had no intention of letting you die.
Why does my queen want you dead?
So what will you do? Will you fulfil Vlaakith's orders? Or will you know the truth?
Not that I ever dreamed I could stop you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot of player walking up to Daisy.

Text.Value: Vlaakith wants me dead because I know Her secret.
I know a secret that Vlaakith never wants to be revealed.
Do your actions have consequences? Yes. Most certainly. But not that one. Not here.
Honest. I like that. But my point is made - you wouldn't understand.
I can see through your lies, creature. You are not Vlaakith.
Go on. Ask your questions.
How is it that you appear to me as my Queen?
I'm no Vlaakith loyalist. Let's get you out of here.
Let's get you out of here before she finds out I let you live.
You stood in Her presence yourself. Was it not enough to convince you of Her fear? Her desperation?
We could have been so much more. But you had to choose this.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Daisy pulls out the blade. Blood spreads from the wound. They fade into wisps, and vanish into the astral ether.

Text.Value: I may kill you yet. But first, I want answers.
Impressive. You barely took a breath. And you didn't understand half of what you said. Your intellectual capacity is insufficient to know the truth.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Daisy gives you a long stare, unimpressed. Then recovers before speaking.

Text.Value: A marvel of ancient magic. I was concerned only for your comfort.
You were destined to come. Oh, dearest Lae'zel. Could a queen want for a more loyal servant?
I suppose I can't blame you for trying.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: On seeing us, Daisy stands up and turns to face us. With a gesture of the hand, invites us to come closer.

Text.Value: About that - I have regrets.
Good luck.
But perhaps you may yet be reasoned with.
Be warned. The Inquisitor awaits your return from this place with orders to kill you.
In other words, with you alive She'll be after my neck.
You are trying to be clever. And failing. I'm sorry, but you just wouldn't understand.
Let's get you out of here, out of Vlaakith's grasp.
Vlaakith? My eternal Queen. Let the planes know Your glory.
Vlaakith has no intentions of letting you live, Lae'zel. And I have no intention of letting you die.
In truth, I am an adventurer from Baldur's Gate who was infected with an illithid tadpole and seeks to be free of the Absolute.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
Daisy manifests a short sword in mid-air, and with a gesture, the hilt swivels towards the player, inviting them to take it.

Daisy kneels on the ground in front of the player.

Text.Value: Then let it be done. Prepare for death.
I was mistaken. You are beyond reason.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Daisy pulls out the blade. Blood spreads from the wound. They fade into wisps, and vanish into the astral ether.

Text.Value: You misunderstand. The zaith'isk was going to kill you. I couldn't let that happen.
Of course. You've had doubts, Lae'zel. You may not have felt them - but I did, deep in your mind's shadows.
What is this place?
Very well. See for yourself.
What's the secret to defeating the mind flayer empire then?
Well done, child. I am not Vlaakith. But I am your safety and your salvation.
Such a pity. So great is your trust that you cling to mirages.
Queen Vlaakith is lying to you. You think She knows the secret mother Gith used to crush the mind flayer empire.
I'm not going to kill the one who's protecting me.

Synopsis: Avatar Lae'zel meets Daisy in person for the first time. Daisy will invite the player to kill them, knowing that Vlaakith has ordered the player to do so. The player will be able to ask Daisy about the astral prison, the Absolute, and why the gith are after them,
